es up 100 points to 300.<br>
But if i satrt out with the SAME exact HP and only have 150STA when i ding will the HP gain be less than the first one?<br>
So here are the Scenarios....<br>
<br>
Scenario 1: Lvl 2-3 -&gt; 200 STA -&gt; 100 HP-300 HP <br>
Scenario 2: Lvl 2-3 -&gt; 150 STA -&gt; !00 HP-???<br>
<br>
Also, any kind of calculator out there? <p>Check out my stuff....yeah that's about it.<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=488612">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=488612</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mrkorb>MrKorb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/03 8:51:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3062.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://users.easystreet.com/korb/images/korb-annaart-glasses.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_hp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Question about STA</span><hr size=1> Magelo is probably the best stat calculator I can think of offhand.<br>
<br>
I created a new character, gave him 100sta to start out with and then added gear to him to push him up to 200sta, while also avoiding any gear that also had raw HP on it.<br>
<br>
At level 2 his base HP with 100sta is 63.  Add 100sta and it's 78.  A total change of 15hp, or about .15hp per sta point.<br>
At level 3 his base HP with 100sta is 93.  Add 100sta and it's 115. A total change of 22hp, or about .22hp per sta point.<br>
<br>
I then removed 50sta worth of gear and changed his level back.<br>
<br>
At level 2 his base HP with 100sta is 63.  Add 50sta and it's 71.  A total change of 8hp, or about .16hp per sta point.<br>
At level 3 his base HP with 100sta is 93.  Add 50sta and it's 104. A total change of 11hp, or about .22hp per sta point.<br>
<br>
What it basically all comes down to is this: sta gear is crap in lower levels because raw HP gear can fill in one slot what it might take 6 slots of sta gear to do.  Base HP is affected only by your level and your base sta, and has nothing do do with your added sta via gear. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14092"><img src="http://users.easystreet.com/korb/images/eq/korby60-corpse-sig.jpg" border="0"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fvighlander>Fvighlander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/03 9:37:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3062.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_hp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Question about STA</span><hr size=1> Tiamat, I think you're misunderstanding the way you gain hitpoints when you level up. It's not a static amount.<br>
<br>
Instead, the amount if hitpoints you gain PER STAMINA goes up as you level. It doesn't matter what your stamina stat was at the time you actually dinged.<br>
<br>
Maybe I misread your post, but it seemed like you were asking a question expecting EQ to act like some of the old MUDs where getting stat buffs just before you levelled was to your advantage. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573077" target="_blank">Fvighlander</a><br>
